Provincial Health MEC Nomafrench Mbombo says snap visits like these are important to keep standards high. CAPE TOWN - Provincial Health MEC Nomafrench Mbombo has paid a surprise visit to Karl Bremer Hospital as part of a drive to increase standards of delivery at public health facilities.The Karl Bremer Hospital is situated on the border of Cape Town's northern suburbs of Bellville and Parow.It has a 310-bed capacity and offers clinical services, including emergency care, paediatrics and psychiatry.Mbombo says snap visits like these are important to keep standards high.The department has a budget of R21.7 billion for the current financial year, of which Karl Bremer Hospital enjoys R365.8 million to run the facility.